---
import ResourceLayout from '../../components/ResourceLayout.astro';
---

<ResourceLayout
  icon="🚑"
  eyebrow="Urgent and emergency care"
  title="Emergency Care"
  introduction="Learn when to call 911, visit an emergency department, use urgent care, or seek help from a walk-in clinic."
>
  <section>
    <h2>When to call 911</h2>
    <p>
      Call 911 for life-threatening emergencies such as severe difficulty
      breathing, chest pain, signs of stroke, major bleeding, loss of
      consciousness, or a serious injury.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Emergency departments</h2>
    <p>
      Emergency departments are open 24 hours a day and are designed to treat
      serious or potentially life-threatening conditions. Patients are assessed
      by urgency, so the sickest people are seen first.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Urgent care and walk-in clinics</h2>
    <p>
      Urgent care centres and walk-in clinics can help with problems that need
      attention soon but are not life-threatening, such as minor injuries,
      infections, or worsening symptoms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What to bring</h2>
    <p>
      Bring your health card if you have one, a list of medications, allergy
      information, and identification. You can still receive emergency care
      even if you do not have these items with you.
    </p>
  </section>

  <aside class="notice">
    <strong>Do not drive yourself during a serious emergency</strong>
    <p>
      Call 911 when immediate treatment may be needed. Paramedics can begin care
      before you reach the hospital.
    </p>
  </aside>
</ResourceLayout>